    "citation": "Odani 1997 9333104",
    "population": "N: 44 (Japanese) Age: - (1-33) WT: 37.8±19.5 G1 [CYP2C9 wt/wt & CYP2C19 wt/wt] N; 15 G2 [CYP2C9 wt/wt & CYP2C19 wt/m1 or wt/m2] N: 18 G3 [CYP2C9 wt/wt & CYP2C19 m1/m1 or m1/m2] N: 5 G4 [CYP2C9 wt/Leu359 & CYP2C19 wt/wt] N: 3 G5 [CYP2C9 wt/Leu359 & CYP2C19 wt/m1 or wt/m2] N: 3",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“In this study, we examined the genetic polymorphism of CYP2C9 and CYP2C19 and the effect of CYP2C9/19 mutations on the pharmacokinetics of phenytoin among 44 Japanese patients with epilepsy.”",
    "covariates": "Tested: - Included: CYP2C9/19 genotype on V, Km, and Vmax; WT on V",
    "observations": "Significant differences were found in Vmax for groups 4 and 5.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "1 compartment model without absorption and michaelis menten elimination",
    "equations": "Vst=(theta1*(1+eta1))**G1+(theta2*(1+eta1))**G2+(theta3*(1+eta1))**G3+(theta4*(1+eta1))**G4+(theta5*(1+eta1))**G5 Kmst=(theta6*(1+eta6))**G1+(theta7*(1+eta7))**G2+(theta8*(1+eta8))**G3+(theta9*(1+eta9))**G4+(theta10*(1+eta10))**G5 Vmst=(theta11*(1+eta11))**G1+(theta12*(1+eta12))**G2+(theta13*(1+eta13))**G3+(theta14*(1+eta14))**G4+(theta15*(1+eta15))**G5 SIZE=42*((WT/42)**1.463) Vm=Vmst*SIZE*(1+eta1) V=Vst*SIZE*(1+eta2) Km=Kmst*(1+eta3) CL=(Vm-(DD/Tau))/Km Cipred=(D/V)*exp(-(CL/V)*time)/(1-exp(-(CL/V)*time)) Cobs=Cipred*(1+eps1) Formulae were converted from mg/day/kg to mg/day for ease of use. G1 is belonging to genetic group 2 (0=no; 1=yes) G2 is belonging to genetic group 2 (0=no; 1=yes) G3 is belonging to genetic group 3 (0=no; 1=yes) G4 is belonging to genetic group 4 (0=no; 1=yes) G5 is belonging to genetic group 2 (0=no; 1=yes)",
